May be an image of french fries, burger and text that says 'Are They Going To Mandate People Stop Eating McDonald's? 7 ingredients that impact the immune system Soybean Oil White Sugar M Carrageenan Cellulose Gum Enriched Wheat Flour High Fructose Corn Syrup Polysorbate 80 FOOD BABE Vani Hari'.

node.text:
This is interesting. What’s your opinion? 

Reposting the @thefoodbabe 

This idea seems to have been lost in the current conversation: 

What you eat has a dramatic effect on your immune system.

If you want to boost your immunity, start with your plate.

Pass on the McDonald's, Burger King, and Chick-Fil-A and do this instead…

Eat more vegetables, fruits, whole grains like oats, and wild fish that are high in omega-3’s which are great for your gut health - which is the key to a strong immune system. 

You have the power to do remarkable things for your health each day, simply by choosing how to eat! 

Don’t let all the negative news let you forget this important fact. 

Please spread this message by sharing this to your story and tagging your friends below. 

The world needs this now more than ever!

Photo by FactsofHealth™ on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'NATIONAL SCIENCE GEOGRAPHIC CORONAVIRUS COVERAGE Microbes in your gut may be new recruits in the fight against viruses Microbiologists are looking at ways to fight viral infections, including COVID-19, with the bacteria already living your intestine. How the gut microbiome helps Hundreds of different species of bacteria live in the gut. This community contains an estimated 40 trillion cells, which is slightly more than the number of human cells making up your body. This enormous collective may help ward off viruses through three primary mechanisms: building wall that blocks invaders, deploying advanced weaponry, and providing support to the immune'.

The Native Americans had a system of planting crops where they would plan the corn, beans, and squash in close proximity to one another. This allowed for the corn to give structure for the beans to climb. The beans provided nitrogen for the soil, and the squash helped prevent weeds from growing. This group of crops is known as "The Three Sisters.''.

May be an image of child and text that says 'Breastfeeding for any amount of time linked to lower blood pressure in toddlers, study finds By Sarah Molano, CNN Updated 11:54 AM ET, Wed July 21, 2021 KapapaHR Breastfeeding for any duration is linked to lower blood pressure in toddlers at age 3, the study found.'.

node.text:
Toddlers who were breastfed for any amount of time had lower blood pressure than those who were not breastfed at all, according to a new study, suggesting once again that "breast is best" for health.

The study, published Wednesday in the Journal of the American Heart Association, used data from almost 2,400 children who are part of the CHILD (Canadian Healthy Infant Longitudinal Development) Cohort Study. CHILD is a longitudinal study that tracks the health of thousands of Canadian mothers and their children born between 2009 and 2012.

The study analyzed data on the length of time infants were breastfed and compared it to their blood pressure at age 3. Across the board, breastfed children had lower blood pressure regardless of the amount of time spent breastfeeding. (via: CNN)

node.text:
Here’s my hack to ripen avocados quicker. Bury unripe avocados in rice or place in a brown paper bag and store in a cool dark place like your pantry. Avocados produce ethylene gas, a plant hormone that triggers the ripening process. The rice or paper bag should trap the ethylene, holding it closer to the fruit and helping it ripen faster. Credit @myhealthydish 

#avocado #avocadolover #avocadohack #avocadoplant #foodhacks #foodscience #avocado🥑 #foodexperiment #foodexperience #healthyfats #healthysnacks #ketosnacks

node.text:
An epidemic in the shadow of a pandemic: Drug overdose deaths reach an all-time high in US

More than 93,000 people died from a drug overdose last year, according to provisional data from the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention's National Center for Health Statistics.

This means that 2020 was the deadliest year on record for drug overdoses.

(Via: CNN)

MAKE SURE YOUR FRIENDS ARE AWARE! 

“Johnson & Johnson announced Wednesday that five of its aerosol sunscreen products are being recalled after some samples were found to contain low levels of benzene, a chemical linked to blood cancers such as leukemia.”
